node.text:
Join us this week as we head to the La Mancha region of Spain, with our 2020 Oso Pardo Tempranillo and our 2020 Oso Pardo Bubbly Rosé. The La Mancha region is known for producing drinkable, approachable styles of Tempranillo that have a distinct freshness and an overall, more juicy style. 

This juicy and fresh Tempranillo is also represented in our 2020 Oso Pardo Bubbly Rosé, which is 100% Tempranillo (a bubbly rosé of this grape variety is very, very rare, so this is a taste you won't want to miss)! Both of these fruit-forward wines have very versatile pairings, so grab a bottle (or two) for your next get-together, taco night, or BBQ cookout. ✈️🍷
